All components comply with WCAG 2.1 AA guidelines and Success Criteria. These fall under the [four principles of accessibility](/accessibility/design-system-accessibility) â€“ Perceivable, Operable, Understandable and Robust. Below are some specific ways in which this component follows these principles:

### Perceivable

The pictograms have been developed using the brand colours, however consideration needs to be given to the background colour they are appearing over to ensure colour contrast ratios are met. In WCAG they would be considered either *Graphical Objects* or *User Interface Components* depending on their usage, in either case they must have a contrast ratio of at least 3:1.
